name: Secret Rooftop Bali by Happy Cow Bali - Jimbaran
address: Perumahan Bukit Pratama, Jl. Gong Kebyar No.32, Jimbaran, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80362, Indonesia
review 1: I honestly don’t know how anyone could leave a bad review here. It’s the best restaurant I’ve been to in Bali. Believe me, I’ve been to a lot of amazing places here. Everything was down to a T. Get the set menu. Every dish was superb. Bursting with flavours. The service was amazing, the girls are really welcoming and kind. To top it off, the setting was perfect. 10/10 deffinatly returning
review 2:
I saw this place on a TikTok review and was skeptical about it. But after trying this place, this place is beyond and more.

The food was amazing, the service was top notch, the price was not even that expensive. The sashimis were so fresh. The scallop melts into your mouth. All of the tastes were balanced, almost like its catered to your taste buds

Honestly, one of the best experience I have while visiting Bali. Everyone should definitely visit this place at least once in their lifetime.

No bad review and I don't get how people could leave a bad review.

kudos to the chefs
review 3:
I stumbled upon this hidden gem on Google, a restaurant located in a residential area. It was a bit surprising because initially, I thought it was a standalone restaurant, but it turned out to be situated in a house. The host and chef were very friendly. Despite the simplicity of the restaurant, it was comfortable and charming. Simple yet delightful.

We ordered steak, mushroom soup, and spaghetti. Everything we ordered had an authentic and delicious taste. The chef personally came to greet us, and the hospitality was remarkable. We even received a very generous bonus portion.

Moreover, the prices were very reasonable.

Overall, we were very satisfied with the food and service here. Highly recommended for those who want to try dining in a unique and unconventional setting outside a traditional restaurant.
review 4: Loved that place, felt so far from the noise and stress of the Denpasar City. Had the menu and liked it all. Came for steak but the rest was also very good. Did think they should ask up front how you would like the steak done, it came raw, which was fine with me, but the small Gass burner is not a quality solution if well done is preferred. Service was excellent and you see the Chef check and talk to each customer. Was very personal all of it. Probably you should reserve up front, I was lucky to get a Table. Did get an extra desert, but that's not my motivation to recommend this place. :-)
review 5:
One of the best evenings in Bali and definitely the most delicious steak I've ever had.

You don't just get a Michelin level taste, you get a gastronomic experience. The concept of the restaurant is based on the privacy of the tables, you don't see other guests, you enjoy the evening and the owner treats you to a first class steak and other dishes ❤️ I will remember this evening for the rest of my life, thank you!

name: RedDoorz near Jimbaran Beach
address: Jl. Nuansa Timur XVII No.2, Jimbaran, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1:
Got to be the coolest accommodation I've been to on this trip. A real bohemian style to the place.
Well equipped room with an extra day bed and a super cold fridge. Nice cold air conditioning made it very comfortable.
Helpful friendly staff.
You do need transport at this location though.
I was also a little confused about how they call themselves a bed and breakfast, but they don't serve food. You can however cook your own in the guest kitchen.
Nice little swimming pool but didn't quite look inviting enough for me to get in.
review 2: The place in general is quite good, in a good spot close to many markets and shops. If you have a bike (a must) just minutes away from the different points of interest. It also has a pool but is never clean. During the day and night it could be a little bit noisy because of the motorcycles, cars and trucks passing by. The only problem is that because is quite and old house, you will find many bugs (ants, termites, cockroaches). And one thing that needs to be cleaned urgent are the water tanks. Even though they are not for drink, the sink and shower , in the water, they come out with little bugs, so be aware.
review 3:
It's not so bad, but seems they tried to deceive review readers by making multiple Google map location.
- The location is not for tourist, should not open a hotel business around here.
- The bed's sheet smells like dog's sweat.
- The customer management is not professional enough
- Please leash and don't unstrain your dog !

Everything else is fine and good for me.
- A water dispenser is good
- A refrigerator is good
- WiFi is good
- Room style is good
- Responsibility and treatment are seems good
review 4: We were surprised how big was the room it had an upstairs bedroom with AC  downstairs bathroom small kitchen and sofa. The place itself looks artistic. Ladies working at the hotel were really lovely and helpful.
review 5: Very unique hotel, beautiful, very nice staff, helpful. We rented a motorbike from them at a good price. We enjoyed our stay there. The place was like a small appartement with a couch, a fridge, desk... And they let us use their kitchen to cook so it was definitely a nice place to stay for us. There is an issue with some mice that visited us but they fixed it straight away. It’s an open wooden house so of course there are « visitors ». Don’t forget to put all the food in the fridge

name: Casa De Palma
address: Jl. Nuansa Barat IA No.2, Jimbaran, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1: Very comfortable place to sleep. Feels like home.

name: Bukawa Lodge Jimbaran & The joy cafe
address: Jl. Nuansa Utama Sel. No.4, Benoa, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1: The room is very nice and cozy. the location is perfect. its near campus. local restaurant and free way. the service is more than good. its perfect. Andri is help full and fast response
review 2: Our reservation was canceled a day before our arrival, even though we booked a room a MONTH IN ADVANCE! They didn't provide any reason when we arrived because we didn't even realize they had canceled. They said they're no longer on Agoda. Don't book here!!! Very bad experience, it could happen to you too!
review 3: The owner.. Andri and his family are very nice and helpfull people.. Love to stay here..
review 4: Verry Verry comfortable place in jimbaran and the food at the Bukawa cafe is delicious too!
review 5: recommended, the staff managed like a hotel. i will come back next time

name: Nuansa Kori House 4 Bedrooms
address: Jl. Nuansa Utama Selatan IV, Benoa, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1: Andri was really helpful in guiding us to find this place. The villa was really cozy and pretty. The facilities were impressive, with cool swimming pool outside. However there are several aspects that can be improved. Maybe wardrobe closet & mirror can be added to each room upstairs. The rooms also needed some hangers to dry the towels and clothes. The living room area needed some air conditioning or at least a ceiling fan. Overall, we had a pleasant stay and I recommend this place to anyone who doesn't mind some lacking for the worthy price that you pay.
review 2: Great place to stay with big family or group of friends. It has 4 rooms and private swimming pool. Friendly staff and easy to find in gmaps.
review 3: Nice place. 4 big rooms with 4 queen size beds. WiFi provided. Only thing is living room no air conditioning. Upstairs master bedroom no sink. Downstairs master bedroom has sewage smell if diffuser turned off. If those are rectified, it would be a perfect five.
review 4: TThe place is HUGE and the facilities are pretty much great for an AirBnB. However, as our group consisted of 4 ladies, we were more than concerned when we realized that there's a bunch of young lads (locals) hanging out in the open air living room (of sorts) right in front of our villa (within the villa compound). They looked like the friends of the guy who greeted us when we arrived. These guys were rather noisy though and that noise lasted late into the night.
review 5: Good bed, cleaning well done every day. Helpful owner, working washing machine &ac and ironing stuff. Not the easiest to find but good location since grocery store is close. Bugs inside and a bleed in a roof of kitchen.

name: Mulia Harum Homestay
address: Jl. Nuansa Utama No.30, Jimbaran, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1:
bad place, both the state of the rooms and the attitude of the staff to their duties. They did not return the money for the unexpired month. worst rental experience ever. very cheaper attitude, expected for a place like this.
realtor Lisa ignores messages and calls
review 2: Very good place. Good facilities, beautiful and clean room, feels like home.

name: Kost Mahardika Jimbaran Universitas Udayana (UNUD)
address: Jalan Lingkar Timur Unud, Jl. Merdeka Jl. Blong Poh No.1, Jimbaran, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1:
Been living here for around half a year already and haven't planned to leave yet. Even though it is located far from the big streets making it hard sometimes for online drivers to find the building 😅 Still, a very comfortable boarding house along with a peaceful environment and nice people around. The owner is very friendly, had a dinner together with the others on my first day living here. The owner and the housekeepers are also very respectful while at the same time cares a lot with our security and wellbeing. Lots of friendly cats and dogs around is a plus personally 🥰
Thank you Kost Mahardika!
review 2:
Dear All Visitor,

Please do not contact the phone number other than on the profile since its a scam, and the owner of Mahardika had been put an report repeatedly but hasn't resolved yet by GTeam. Always put your self awarness and be alert. Thank you.

address: Jl. Nuansa Utama, Jimbaran, Kec. Kuta Sel., Denpasar, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1: We went here late night around 9.30pm and it's still open. The food is great with affordable price. But the service is slow. Looks like they're a bit overwhelmed with many orders, and it seems they struggle to keep up which order to go first.
review 2: The most disappointing service in the town goes to this seller. I was starving and really wanted to eat ketoprak but it takes ages to prepared my order. The female seller also should try to apply for Karen's Dinner. She's talented! What a great talent to turn hungry to hangry!
review 3: The food is super good, the taste as same as in Surabaya. This is one of my favorite warung in Jimbaran
review 4: Super authentic taste of surabaya’s cuisine! Not just rawon

review 1: I think it is the best mie SOP ayam i ever tasted. The stock is the main part that complete the noodle, chicken and tofu and as far as i order the mie SOP, the taste is consistent. The portion just right and the price is affordable. The Jengkol is also tasty.
review 2: Tried mi sop and it was tasty. They also sell Badak (Sarsaparilla soda)
review 3: The best of the best, seriously! Even if the price would be 75k for this soup
review 4: Tried mie sop, it was good! Owner was friendly too.

FAVORITE PLACE FOR ICE CAPPUCINO.

JAJO LOVE YOU
review 2: A hidden gem in Jimbaran. It was good coffee and delicious homemade cakes in a residential with very friendly owner and furry friends. 🍂🙂
review 3: Charming hosts, great coffee (Cappuccino, Latte, Vietnamese Drip, Iced), cakes and snacks, nice place to hang out and relax! 😊
review 4: Great coffee, the best apple pie, cozy ambience
review 5:
Five times yes so: Yes, yes, yes, yes and yes.
It's like home and it's adorable as well as cute. There are only two tables and a few chairs ;-). Next time I come with my bike because Jajo is also a cyclist. Incredible apple pie and very good coffee, a place where you feel good. Makasih Mas ya, matur nuwon.
Alex
